<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="94.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,222,248]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[322,531,222,248]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
placed this species in his 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[820,943,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[820,943,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1125,1295,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[1125,1295,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[194,280,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[194,280,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara &amp; Okutani" authorityYear="1983" box="[369,637,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapporensis">
<emphasis box="[369,637,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Pamphilius sapporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has much in common with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[956,1080,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[956,1080,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in morphology, molecular data (see below) and host plants, and overlapping distributions of the two species in 
<collectingRegion box="[1033,1143,294,320]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
is interesting in clarifying their speciation history. The maximum intraspecific 
<emphasis box="[748,762,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">p</emphasis>
-distance among the three Japanese specimens in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara &amp; Okutani" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapporensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. sapporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 0.3% in COI and 0.1% in NaK and the nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Konow" authorityYear="1897" box="[981,1112,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteatus">
<emphasis box="[981,1112,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. balteatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 2.5% in the COI analysis, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[487,610,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[487,610,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a minimum of 0.8% in the NaK analysis. In the COI tree (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1383,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 149" captionStartId="236.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[169,1416,198,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@236.[163,1425,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="236" captionText="FIGURE 149. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876861/files/figure.png" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Fig. 149</figureCitation>
), the relationship of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara &amp; Okutani" authorityYear="1983" box="[318,477,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapporensis">
<emphasis box="[318,477,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. sapporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with other species was not well resolved, but in the NaK tree (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1258,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 161" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[177,1403,189,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@246.[171,1417,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 161. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876886/files/figure.png" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Fig. 161</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara &amp; Okutani" authorityYear="1983" box="[1277,1436,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapporensis">
<emphasis box="[1277,1436,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. sapporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was retrieved as the sister of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[476,600,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[476,600,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 99% UFBoot support.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="94.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
In 
<collectingRegion box="[229,342,510,536]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[352,419,511,537]" name="Japan" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Japan</collectingCountry>
, this species occurs together with two other 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kangas &amp; Syrjanen" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[907,1038,510,536]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Filipendula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[907,1038,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Filipendula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-associated pamphiliids, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1313,1436,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[1313,1436,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(known from 
<collectingRegion box="[309,422,546,572]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, Honshu and Shikoku) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Benes" authorityYear="1972" box="[743,1037,546,572]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kumamotonis">
<emphasis box="[743,1037,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Onycholyda kumamotonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(known from Sakhalin, 
<collectingRegion box="[1319,1432,546,572]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, Kunashiri Is., Honshu and?Kyushu). The largely orange upper part of head will easily distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara &amp; Okutani" authorityYear="1983" box="[1275,1436,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapporensis">
<emphasis box="[1275,1436,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. sapporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the latter two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
